  {
    "tour": 2,
    "title": "Tales from Asia",
    "host": "Storyteller",
    "intro": "Perhaps you've heard Aesop's fable about how the slow and steady tortoise won a race against the quick but flighty hare. Or maybe someone told you about the man who pulled a thorn from a lion's paw and won his eternal friendship. These tales, and many others besides, came from Asia. They've been translated into so many languages and have so many versions that it's almost impossible to say who told the story first.",
